article.headline: Bird adds 18 points, five assists for Storm
article.linkText: Jackson scores 21 as Storm rout Silver Stars
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Lauren Jackson scored a season-high 21 points to
lead the Seattle Storm to a 79-51 victory over the San Antonio
Silver Stars on Sunday night.

After missing her first four shots, Jackson finished 8-of-16
from the field and made all five of her free throws.

"We totally took them out of their game," Jackson said. "It
felt really good to have a full game."

Sue Bird had 18 points and Betty Lennox added 12 for the Storm
(2-1). Bird made 4-of-5 from 3-point range, had five assists and no
turnovers.

Bird was quick to praise Jackson.

"Pretty much everything we run goes through her," Bird said.
"When she plays like the way she did tonight, it makes it easier
for everyone else. She opens up so much for the rest of the team."

Storm coach Anne Donovan agreed.

"(Jackson) is just one of the most complete players I've ever
coached," Donovan said. "Inside, outside and so strong right now.
And the combination with Betty and Sue on the perimeter, where do
you put your focus defensively if you're an opposing coach?"

Wendy Palmer-Daniel had nine points for the Silver Stars (0-4),
who shot 38 percent from the floor and had 20 turnovers.

Seattle made only 5-of-17 shots in the first 10 minutes, but
never trailed by more than two points.

After a jumper by San Antonio's LaToya Thomas tied the game at
15 with 12 minutes left, Seattle went on a 15-0 run. The Storm had
eight points from the free-throw line during the spree.

The Silver Stars went 9 minutes without a field goal to help
Seattle to a 36-25 halftime lead.

"I give credit to Seattle," Silver Stars coach Dan Hughes
said. "I thought they played very well, and I give credit to
Jackson. She really competed and was physical down low on the
block. That's the reason why this Seattle team was successful the
past two years."
